|[[NTT DoCoMo]]
|{{flag|Japan}}
|{{dts|February 2007}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nttdocomo.com/pr/2007/001319.html |title=NTT DoCoMo Achieves World's First 5 Gbit/s Packet Transmission in 4G Field Experiment |publisher=NTT DoCoMo |access-date=2008-09-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080925084229/http://www.nttdocomo.com/pr/2007/001319.html |archive-date=2008-09-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The operator announced the completion of a 4G trial where it achieved a maximum [[Packet (information technology)|packet]] transmission rate of approximately 5&nbsp;Gbit/s in the downlink using 12 transmit and 12 receive antennas and 100&nbsp;MHz frequency bandwidth to a mobile station moving at 10&nbsp;km/h.
|-
|[[Agilent Technologies]]
|{{flag|Spain}}
|{{dts|February 2011}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.agilent.com/about/newsroom/presrel/2011/02feb-em11015.html |title=Agilent Technologies Introduces Industry's First LTE-Advanced Signal Generation, Analysis Solutions |publisher=Agilent |access-date=2011-04-11 |archive-date=2011-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928045704/http://www.agilent.com/about/newsroom/presrel/2011/02feb-em11015.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> The vendor demonstrated at [[Mobile World Congress]] the industry's first test solutions for LTE-Advanced with both [[Signal generator|signal generation]] and [[Spectrum analyzer|signal analysis]] solutions.
|-
|[[Ericsson]]
|{{flag|Sweden}}
|{{dts|June 2011}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telecompaper.com/news/ericsson-demonstrates-lte-advanced-in-sweden--812081 |title=Ericsson demonstrates LTE Advanced in Sweden |publisher=Telecompaper |date=2011-06-28 |access-date=2014-08-13}}</ref> The vendor demonstrated LTE-Advanced in [[Kista]].
|-
|[[mtc touch|touch]]
|{{flag|Lebanon}}
|{{dts|April 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2013/04/08/touch-huawei-trial-250mbps-lte-fdd-800mhz1800mhz-carrier-aggregation/ |title=Touch, Huawei trial 250Mbps LTE FDD 800MHz/1800MHz carrier aggregation |publisher=TeleGeography |date=2013-04-08 |access-date=2014-08-24}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with Chinese vendor [[Huawei]] and combined 800&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 1.8&nbsp;GHz spectrum. touch achieved 250 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Vodafone New Zealand|Vodafone]]
|{{flag|New Zealand}}
|{{dts|May 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/business/news/article.cfm?c_id=3&objectid=10885874 |title=Vodafone shows off next-gen mobile broadband |publisher=NZ Herald |date=2013-05-24}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with [[Nokia Siemens|Nokia Networks]] and combined 1.8&nbsp;GHz spectrum and 700&nbsp;MHz spectrum. Vodafone achieved just below 300 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[mobilkom Austria|A1]]
|{{flag|Austria}}
|{{dts|June 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mobileeurope.co.uk/Press-Wire/a1-telekom-austria-demos-580mbps-lte-a-speeds-with-ericsson-nsn-hardware |title=A1 TELEKOM AUSTRIA DEMOS 580MBPS LTE-A SPEEDS WITH ERICSSON, NSN HARDWARE |publisher=Mobile Europe |date=2013-06-06 |access-date=2014-04-30}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with [[Ericsson]] and [[Nokia Solutions and Networks|NSN]] using 4x4 MIMO. A1 achieved 580 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Turkcell]]
|{{flag|Turkey}}
|{{dts|August 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2013/08/02/turkish-delight-turkcell-unveils-900mbps-transmission-speeds-in-lte-a-trial/ |title=Turkish delight? Turkcell unveils 900Mbps transmission speeds in LTE-A trial |publisher=TeleGeography |date=2013-08-02 |access-date=2014-11-14}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Istanbul]] with Chinese vendor Huawei. Turkcell achieved 900 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Telstra]]
|{{flag|Australia}}
|{{dts|August 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ericsson.com/news/1722258 |title=World's first commercial LTE-Advanced call on 1800MHz and 900MHz |publisher=Ericsson |date=2013-08-12 |access-date=2014-04-30}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with Swedish vendor Ericsson and combined 900&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 1.8&nbsp;GHz spectrum.
|-
|[[Smart Communications|SMART]]
|{{flag|Philippines}}
|{{dts|August 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite news |title=200MBPS IN DAVAO - Smart tests LTE-Advanced system down south. |author=J.M. Tuazon |url=http://www.interaksyon.com/infotech/200mbps-in-davao-smart-tests-lte-advanced-system-down-south |newspaper=Interaksyon |date=21 August 2013 |access-date=21 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130821163111/http://www.interaksyon.com/infotech/200mbps-in-davao-smart-tests-lte-advanced-system-down-south |archive-date=21 August 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with Chinese vendor Huawei and combined 2.1&nbsp;GHz spectrum and 1.80&nbsp;GHz spectrum bands and achieved 200 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[SoftBank Mobile|SoftBank]]
|{{flag|Japan}}
|{{dts|September 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2013/09/13/softbanks-trial-lte-a-in-3-5ghz-band-achieves-770mbps/ |title=Softbank's trial LTE-A in 3.5GHz band achieves 770Mbps |publisher=TeleGeography |date=2013-09-13 |access-date=2014-08-13}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Tokyo]] with Chinese vendor Huawei. Softbank used the 3.5&nbsp;GHz spectrum band and achieved 770 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[beCloud]]/ [[Mobile TeleSystems|MTS]]
|{{flag|Belarus}}
|{{dts|October 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2013/10/10/becloud-to-test-lte-a/ |title=beCloud to test LTE-A |publisher=TeleGeography |date=2013-10-10 |access-date=2014-08-13}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with Chinese vendor Huawei.
|-
|[[SFR]]
|{{flag|France}}
|{{dts|October 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fiercewireless.com/europe/story/sfr-completes-first-lte-advanced-trials-france/2013-10-18 |title=SFR completes 'first' LTE Advanced trials in France |publisher=FierceWirelessEurope |date=2013-10-18 |access-date=2014-04-30}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Marseille]] and combined 800&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 2.6&nbsp;GHz spectrum. SFR achieved 174 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[EE (telecommunications company)|EE]]
|{{flag|United Kingdom}}
|{{dts|November 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telecoms.com/195031/ee-launches-worlds-fastest-lte-a-network-in-london/ |title=EE launches 'world's fastest' LTE-A network in London |publisher=Telecoms.com |date=2013-11-05 |access-date=2013-12-27}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[London]] with Chinese vendor Huawei and combined 20&nbsp;MHz of 1.8&nbsp;GHz spectrum and 20&nbsp;MHz of 2.6&nbsp;GHz spectrum. EE achieved 300 Mbit/s which is equal to category 6 LTE.
|-
|[[Telefónica Germany|O<sub>2</sub>]]
|{{flag|Germany}}
|{{dts|November 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telefonica.de/press/press-releases/network/news/5342/now-available-at-telefonica-the-fastest-lte-radio-cell-in-germany-and-mobile-vo-lte-in-live-network.html |title=Now available at Telefónica: The fastest LTE radio cell in Germany and mobile VoLTE in live network |publisher=Telefónica |date=2013-11-14 |access-date=2014-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003075151/https://www.telefonica.de/press/press-releases/network/news/5342/now-available-at-telefonica-the-fastest-lte-radio-cell-in-germany-and-mobile-vo-lte-in-live-network.html |archive-date=2017-10-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Munich]] with Chinese vendor Huawei and combined 10&nbsp;MHz of 800&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 20&nbsp;MHz of 2.6&nbsp;GHz spectrum. O<sub>2</sub> achieved 225 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[SK Telecom]]
|{{flag|South Korea}}
|{{dts|November 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.sktworld.co.kr/4209#fb |title=[넓고 빠른 광대역 LTE-A] #1. 3배 빠른 광대역 LTE-A 시대가 열린다! |publisher=SK Telecom |language=ko |date=2013-11-28 |access-date=2014-05-16 |archive-date=2014-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517122023/http://blog.sktworld.co.kr/4209#fb |url-status=dead }}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced and combined 10&nbsp;MHz of 850&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 20&nbsp;MHz of 1.8&nbsp;GHz spectrum. SK Telecom achieved 225 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Vodafone Germany|Vodafone]]
|{{flag|Germany}}
|{{dts|November 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vodafone.de/unternehmen/presse/225594-219883.html |title=Vodafone zeigt in Dresden das schnellste Mobilfunknetz der Republik |publisher=Vodafone |language=de |date=2013-11-15 |access-date=2014-04-30}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Dresden]] with Swedish vendor Ericsson and combined 10&nbsp;MHz of 800&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 20&nbsp;MHz of 2.6&nbsp;GHz spectrum. Vodafone achieved 225 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Telstra]]
|{{flag|Australia}}
|{{dts|December 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.computerworld.com.au/article/533656/telstra_hits_300_mbps_lte-a_trial/?eid=-255 |title=Telstra hits 300 Mbps in LTE-A trial |publisher=Computerworld |date=2013-12-06 |access-date=2014-03-24 |archive-date=2019-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211183810/https://www.computerworld.com.au/article/533656/telstra_hits_300_mbps_lte-a_trial/?eid=-255 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with Swedish vendor Ericsson and combined 20&nbsp;MHz of 1.8&nbsp;GHz spectrum and 20&nbsp;MHz of 2.6&nbsp;GHz spectrum. Telstra achieved 300 Mbit/s which is equal to category 6 LTE.
|-
|[[Optus]]
|{{flag|Australia}}
|{{dts|December 2013}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.itnews.com.au/News/368041,optus-tests-td-lte-carrier-aggregation-in-melbourne.aspx |title=Optus tests TD-LTE carrier aggregation in Melbourne |publisher=iTnews |date=2013-12-19 |access-date=2014-03-29}}</ref> The operator trialed [[TD-LTE]]-Advanced with Chinese vendor Huawei and combined two 20&nbsp;MHz channels of 2.3&nbsp;GHz spectrum. Optus achieved over 160 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Entel Chile]]
|{{flag|Chile}}
|{{dts|September 2015}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bnamericas.com/en/news/telecommunications/entel-chile-carries-out-first-lte-a-trial/ |title=Entel Chile carries out first LTE-A trial |publisher=BNAmericas |date=2015-09-22 |access-date=2018-04-10}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Rancagua]] using 15&nbsp;MHz of 700 MHz and 20&nbsp;MHz of 2600&nbsp;MHz spectrum, achieving over 200 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Claro Brasil]]
|{{flag|Brazil}}
|{{dts|December 2015}}
|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telesintese.com.br/claro-faz-primeiro-teste-externo-com-lte-advanced-na-faixa-de-700-mhz/ |title=Claro faz primeiro teste externo com LTE Advanced na faixa de 700&nbsp;MHz |publisher=Telesintese |date=2015-12-15 |access-date=2016-03-29}}</ref> The [[Claro Brasil]] presented in Rio Verde the first tests with 4.5G technology, LTE Advanced, which offers an internet speed of up to 300Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Advanced Info Service|AIS]]
|{{Flag|Thailand}}
|March 2016
|<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lteto5g.com/ais-launches-the-worlds-first-4-5g-network-in-thailand/|title=AIS launches the world's first 4.5G network in Thailand|date=2016-03-24|access-date=2017-12-26|language=en-US}}</ref> The operator launched the first 4.5G on [[LTE-U|LTE-U/LAA]] network in [[Bangkok]] with the combination of 1800&nbsp;MHz spectrum and 2100&nbsp;MHz spectrum using [[Carrier Aggregation]] (CA), 4x4 [[MIMO]], [[Quadrature amplitude modulation|DL256QAM/UL64QAM]] and the use of [[LTE-Unlicensed]] ([[LTE-U]]) to facilitate high-speed network. AIS achieved download speed up to 784.5 Mbit/s and upload speed 495 Mbit/s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://droidsans.com/ais-next-g-gigabit-network-ready/|title=Take tour on the new AIS Next-G ready network|access-date=2017-12-27|language=th-TH}}</ref> This was made possible by Joint Development Center (JIC) the special R&D program between [[Advanced Info Service|AIS]] and [[Huawei]].
|-
|[[MagtiCom]]
|{{flag|Georgia}}
|May 2016
|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lteto5g.com/magticom-launches-lte-advanced-network-georgia/|title=MagtiCom launches LTE-Advanced network in Georgia|website=www.ucom.am|access-date=2016-06-06}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced in [[Tbilisi]] and combined the 800&nbsp;MHz with its existing 1800&nbsp;MHz spectrum. MagtiCom achieved download speed 185 Mbit/s and upload speed 75 Mbit/s.
|-
|[[Ucom]]
|{{flag|Armenia}}
|September 2016
|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ucom.am/en/news/2016/09/24/4g+/68|title=Ucom Deployed Ericsson's Latest 4G+ Technology for the First Time in Armenia|website=www.ucom.am|access-date=2017-02-06}}</ref> The operator trialed LTE-Advanced with Swedish vendor Ericsson. Ucom achieved 250 Mbit/s download speed which is equal to category 6 LTE.
|-
|[[Altel]]
|{{flag|Kazakhstan}}
|April 2017
|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dknews.kz/business/36-telecom/14722-altel-zapustil-v-kommercheskuyu-ekspluatatsiyu-tekhnologiyu-lte-advanced-4g.html|title=Altel: LTE-Advanced (4G+) Technology for the First Time in Kazakhstan|website=dknews.kz|access-date=2017-04-04|archive-date=2017-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170405172320/http://dknews.kz/business/36-telecom/14722-altel-zapustil-v-kommercheskuyu-ekspluatatsiyu-tekhnologiyu-lte-advanced-4g.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> The operator launched LTE-Advanced in 12 cities across Kazakhstan. Altel achieved 225 Mbit/s download speed. LTE-Advanced (4G+) Technology is up to be launched in 5 more cities in Kazakhstan in May 2017.
|-
|[[List of mobile network operators of Europe#Latvia|Bite Latvija]]
|{{Flag|Latvia}}
|September 2016
|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bite.lv/lv/ieskandinot-baltijas-bundzinieku-samitu-bite-jaudigi-atklaj-pirmo-45g-tiklu-latvija|title=By sounding off the Baltic Drummers' Summit, Bite unveils the first 4.5G network in Latvia with power|access-date=2017-09-18|language=lv}}</ref> The operator launched 8 4.5G cell stations in [[Riga]] after testing in partnership with [[Huawei]] and the [[Riga Technical University]] on June 15, 2017.
|-
|[[Wi-tribe Pakistan|Wi-Tribe]]
|{{Flag|Pakistan}}
|May 2017
|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://propakistani.pk/2017/08/28/wi-tribe-becomes-pakistans-first-operator-cross-200mbps-internet-speeds/|title=Wi-tribe Becomes Pakistan's First Operator to Cross 200Mbps Internet Speeds|date=2017-08-28|access-date=2017-10-11|language=en-US}}</ref> The operator first tested their LTE-A network in May 2017 over the 3.5&nbsp;GHz band, and it was then made officially available in Lahore, Pakistan, with more cities to follow. Wi-Tribe achieved speeds of up to 200 Mbit/s over their new LTE-A network. This was done using equipment from [[Huawei 4G eLTE|Huawei]].
|-
|[[Telcel]]
|{{Flag|Mexico}}
|March 2018
|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/estilo/llega-mexico-gigared-4-5g-telcel|title=Llega a México la GigaRed 4.5G de Telcel|date=March 14, 2018|website=Grupo Milenio}}</ref> The operator offered the service in [[Mexico City]] and other 10 cities nationwide on March 14, 2018.
|-
|[[Airtel]]
|{{flag|India}}
|April 2012
|On 10 April 2012, Airtel launched 4G services through dongles and modems using TD-LTE technology in Kolkata, becoming the first company in India to offer 4G services. The Kolkata launch was followed by launches in Bangalore (7 May 2012), Pune (18 October 2012), and Chandigarh, Mohali and Panchkula (25 March 2013).
|}
